name: AS1597.1-2010 & AS1597.2-2013, Clause 2.9.2 - Size Dimensions (Internal Measurements) Internal span and heights measurements of a culvert unit and span of a link or base slab are taken 200mm from each end and at the middle length of the culvert. The size dimension shall be taken from the mean of the 3 values.

Deck - AS1597.1-2010 & AS1597.2-2013, Clause 2.9.3 - Thickness - The thickness of the culvert crown unit, link or base slab shall be determined by taking measurements at 300mm in from both sides and the middle at either ends of the product. The thickness shall be taken as the mean of the six values.

Top of Leg - AS1597.1-2010 & AS1597.2-2013, Clause 2.9.3 - Thickness - The thickness of the culvert unit legs shall be measured at the junction of the haunch and the top of the legs, and 300mm from end of the unit. The leg thickness at each horizontal plane shall be taken as the mean of the four values.

Bottom of Leg - AS1597.1-2010 & AS1597.2-2013, Clause 2.9.3 - Thickness - The thickness of the culvert unit legs shall be measured 50mm up from the base of the legs, and 300mm from end of the unit. The leg thickness at each horizontal plane shall be taken as the mean of the four values.

AS1597.1-2010 & AS1597.2-2013, Clause 2.9.5 - Length - The length of the precast unit shall be measured at the base of each leg and across the middle of the span. The length dimension shall be determined as the mean of the 3 values.
*AS1597.2-2013, Clause 2.10.3.1 – Ends - The end faces of the culvert unit, link or base slab at any location shall be square within +4mm
*AS1597.2-2013, Clause 2.10.3.2 – Vertically - The culvert unit, base or link slab shall not deviate from the vertical at any location by more than +20mm for the entire overall height of the culvert
*AS1597.2-2013, Clause 2.10.3.3 – Squareness - The plan diagonals of the culvert unit, link or base slab and the side elevation diagonals of each culvert unit leg shall not differ by more than +20mm.

name: APPARATUS: Cover Meter - Device capable of detecting the presence of reinforcement and indicating the depth from the concrete surface to the nearest point on the surface of the reinforcement with an accuracy of +1mm, at a depth of 20mm.
Calibration of meter - Calibrate the meter in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions
(a) Calibrate the cover meter in accordance with the manufacturer’s instructions.
(b) Select the location for conducting measurements along a line corresponding to the locations for chase specified below:
(A) Crown - On soffit and top at the ends and middle of the span.
(B) Legs - On each side per leg 200 mm vertically up from the base, at mid-height and at the junction of the inside corner haunch.
(ii) Link and base slabs - On soffit and top at the ends and midpoint of the span.
(c) Move the cover meter in a line parallel to the length of the specimen at each location selected in Step (b) above.
(d) Mark on the surface the position of two consecutive reinforcement bars or wires.
(e) Move the meter slowly backward and forward in the same line at each marked position.
(f) Record the minimum value of the cover indicated.

name: APPARATUS: Cover Meter - Device capable of detecting the presence of reinforcement and indicating the depth from the concrete surface to the nearest point on the surface of the reinforcement with an accuracy of +1mm, at a depth of 20mm.
Calibration of meter - Calibrate the meter in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions

A5.3 Cover testing A routine test for concrete cover should be performed at a frequency of 1 per 200 items produced to the same design but not less frequently than one per two months. If the test specimen fails, a further two samples should be selected at random from two components of the same type and batch as represented by the original test piece. Should one or both samples fail, the customer may reject components from the batch and may also specify that the frequency of testing be increased to 1 per 50 items produced or one of each week’s production until it can be demonstrated, by five consecutive complying tests, that the specified limit for test failure is not being exceeded.
D5.1.1 Location of chases On each sample component, the number and position of the chases required are as follows:

(a) For circularly reinforced components, one external and one internal chase are spaced apart by one quarter of the external surface circumference, along the direction of the component’s longitudinal axis.
(b) For access covers and conversion slabs, two chases are cut at right angles to each other for each layer of reinforcement.

D5.2.2 Procedure Move the meter in a line corresponding to the locations for chases given in Paragraph D5.1.1, marking on the surface the position of two consecutive main reinforcing bars. Move the meter slowly backward and forward in the same line at each marked position and record the minimum value of cover indicated.
